Package assegnamento3.src

Class DatabaseManager

java.lang.Object
assegnamento3.src.DatabaseManager
public class DatabaseManager
extends java.lang.Object
The class DatabaseManager handles the persistence of the data.

Creates a connection to the database and implements the methods for saving wine, user, order, notification, and message lists as well as loading them back from main memory.

    • DatabaseManager

      public DatabaseManager​(java.lang.String url, java.lang.String args, java.lang.String user, java.lang.String password) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Class constructor.

      Initializes the connection to the database and creates the tables if not already present.

      A default Admin "m.rossi@gmail.com" with password "1234" is created.

      A default Seller "g.bianchi@gmail.com" with password "1234" is created.

      A default list of Wines is provided.

      Parameters:
      url - url of db
      args - arguments
      user - user
      password - password
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - Invalid sql
